[1]
Date: Tue 15 Jun 2010
Source: OIE Weekly Disease Information 2010; 23(24) [abridged, edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9373>


Foot and mouth disease, Japan: follow up report no 9
----------------------------------------------------
Information received on 15 Jun 2010 from Dr Toshiro Kawashima, CVO, Animal
Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo, Japan

This report covers 10 new outbreaks of FMDV serotype O in the Miyazaki
prefecture. Their respective details, including start dates, species, and
number, in each of them, of susceptible animals, clinical cases and culled
animals, are to be found in the above URL.

Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 4601 / 10 / 0 / 4601 / 0
Cattle / 2597 / 18 / 0 / 2597 / 0

Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s):
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated / Details
MIYAZAKI / Cattle / 45 944 / Oil-adjuvant killed vaccine against type O.
MIYAZAKI / Swine / 79 603 / Oil-adjuvant killed vaccine against type O.

The following epidemiological comments were included:
"Four outbreaks occurred outside (but nearby) a movement control area
around Kawaminami-cho in Miyazaki prefecture. All the cases showed typical
clinical signs and were confirmed by PCR.

"A movement restriction within 10 km around the outbreak in Saito city
(start date 21 May 2010) was lifted on 13 Jun 2010 because there has been
no outbreak in the area since 23 May 2010."

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[An interactive map, showing the locations of all 289 outbreaks confirmed
in Miyazaki since 20 Apr 2010 is available at
